title: Police: 1 hurt in Dubuque crash
text: Police said one person was injured in a single-vehicle crash in Dubuque. Dakes O. Current conditions in Dubuque, IA Police said one person was injured in a single-vehicle crash in Dubuque. Dakes O. Eliam, 59, of Maquoketa, Iowa, was transported by ambulance to UnityPoint Health-Finley Hospital for treatment of his injuries, according to Dubuque police. Police reported that Eliam was driving north on U.S. 61 near the U.S. 151 exit at approximately 5:45 a.m. Thursday, when he fell asleep at the wheel. The vehicle left the roadway and struck four poles holding a cable guard rail.
